text: Kain-Yelga () is a rural locality (a village) in Subkhankulovsky Selsoviet, Tuymazinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 119 as of 2010. There are 10 streets. == Geography == It is located 10 km from Tuymazy, 5 km from Subkhankulovo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Tuymazinsky District
title: Kain-Yelga, Tuymazinsky District, Republic of Bashkortostan
